Infinite greatness is infinite honor, infinite pride; 
Infinite great, infinite unending; 
Infinite deep, infinite self-respect, 
Who poet does not determine.

Here is the translation:

Tree branch palang khurashi, Jiaan beetha Shrihiri hoolsi;
Khel lokik aloolik kare, nave paar lakyaa tano sere.

He performs Leela above, like a grateful mind; 
A grateful one enjoys, plays, and laughs with glee, 
when the brush touches, what does it convey?

Written as it is:

Lakhaye Lamboodar kar nathi, suune Prithu Sam kan kyaanthi;
Nathi Ayush Lomash tani, nathi Buddhi te Vidhi thi Ghani.

Here is the translation:

"Speak it out now with enthusiasm, illumination to a worn-out soul; 
Many are lost in my own house, writing a beautiful life story."
